Based on the analysis of FortiGuard Labs, Enemybot is Keksecs latest tool for performing DDoS attacks.

To protect itself, it uses simple obfuscation techniques on its strings as well as hosting its C2 server in the Tor network, taking advantage of the networks anonymity. It uses several techniques commonly found in other DDoS botnet malware to infect other devices.
